1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,350
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,350 --> 00:00:02,650
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,383 --> 00:00:05,550
(Episode 63)

4
00:00:07,483 --> 00:00:10,850
Why are you back?
I thought you had something come up.

5
00:00:10,883 --> 00:00:13,583
I'm sorry I couldn't finish the meeting.

6
00:00:13,950 --> 00:00:15,083
That's okay.

7
00:00:15,483 --> 00:00:17,850
Don't tell me you came back to work.

8
00:00:17,850 --> 00:00:19,650
I had to.
I couldn't focus on work today...

9
00:00:19,650 --> 00:00:21,850
because of a personal matter. Bye then.

10
00:00:22,250 --> 00:00:23,250
Wait, Manager Seo.

11
00:00:24,750 --> 00:00:26,650
- Let's take a walk.
- Sorry?

12
00:00:27,050 --> 00:00:29,050
You don't have to work only at your desk.

13
00:00:30,283 --> 00:00:34,183
We can talk about work as we walk
and clear up some misunderstandings.

14
00:00:38,750 --> 00:00:39,783
I'm adopted.

15
00:00:41,350 --> 00:00:44,450
On the way home from that birthday party,

16
00:00:45,550 --> 00:00:47,850
my father died in an accident.

17
00:00:50,383 --> 00:00:52,050
That's why I couldn't keep my promise...

18
00:00:52,050 --> 00:00:54,050
to come to that playground every Saturday.

19
00:00:55,250 --> 00:00:58,050
After that, I moved
between relatives' homes and orphanages,

20
00:00:58,783 --> 00:01:01,850
until my grandpa adopted me
as CEO Ko Dae Chi's son.

21
00:01:04,050 --> 00:01:05,050
Team Manager.

22
00:01:05,883 --> 00:01:08,550
This is everything...

23
00:01:08,550 --> 00:01:10,783
I never got to tell you.

24
00:01:12,450 --> 00:01:15,483
I don't have any secrets from you anymore.

25
00:01:19,850 --> 00:01:21,783
It couldn't have been easy to tell me.

26
00:01:24,050 --> 00:01:27,183
I'm sorry. I had no idea.

27
00:01:31,583 --> 00:01:32,983
So it was all my misunderstanding?

28
00:01:33,083 --> 00:01:34,250
Yes, it was.

29
00:01:34,983 --> 00:01:37,950
I never asked Mr. Han Ji Hun
to do anything like that.

30
00:01:38,983 --> 00:01:39,983
Chief.

31
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:41,350
To be honest,

32
00:01:42,350 --> 00:01:45,350
I was really angry that day
that you had misunderstood me like that.

33
00:01:46,450 --> 00:01:50,283
But then I realized
you had every reason to think that.

34
00:01:52,083 --> 00:01:54,250
Anyone can see that I can't beat Gyeol
based on skill alone,

35
00:01:54,950 --> 00:01:56,283
yet I am willing to do anything...

36
00:01:57,550 --> 00:02:00,883
to win this competition.

37
00:02:02,150 --> 00:02:03,250
That's not it.

38
00:02:04,083 --> 00:02:06,850
I heard what you said to Mr. Han Ji Hun...

39
00:02:06,850 --> 00:02:08,750
in front of Ms. Cho Eun Ae's desk.

40
00:02:09,150 --> 00:02:10,283
Of course I want to win.

41
00:02:11,050 --> 00:02:13,250
I've put everything in my life on the line
for this competition.

42
00:02:14,650 --> 00:02:16,183
If you want to win that badly,

43
00:02:16,850 --> 00:02:19,750
think carefully
about what you should really be doing.

44
00:02:22,650 --> 00:02:24,850
I guess anyone could've misunderstood
in that situation.

45
00:02:25,350 --> 00:02:28,783
I'm sorry. I apologize
for what I said on the rooftop.

46
00:02:29,850 --> 00:02:31,383
Seo Seung Ri is apologizing to me?

47
00:02:33,350 --> 00:02:35,950
You're someone who never gives people
a reason to apologize,

48
00:02:35,950 --> 00:02:39,450
so hearing you apologize feels strange.

49
00:02:40,283 --> 00:02:41,850
I have a lot to apologize for these days.

50
00:02:42,550 --> 00:02:45,750
Not just to you, but to someone else too.

51
00:02:46,483 --> 00:02:47,483
Who besides me?

52
00:02:51,250 --> 00:02:52,350
What's wrong now?

53
00:02:54,183 --> 00:02:56,850
These days, it feels like you're not
the Seo Seung Ri I used to know.

54
00:02:57,350 --> 00:02:58,650
You seem like
a completely different person.

55
00:02:59,850 --> 00:03:00,850
You're right.

56
00:03:01,950 --> 00:03:03,950
I don't even know
who Seo Seung Ri really is anymore.

57
00:03:05,283 --> 00:03:06,583
What do you mean by that?

58
00:03:08,250 --> 00:03:10,183
Everything about me feels fake.

59
00:03:11,350 --> 00:03:14,083
Not just me, but everything around me...

60
00:03:15,950 --> 00:03:17,650
that I've always believed in.

61
00:03:18,283 --> 00:03:21,650
There's something else going on
besides Gyeol, isn't there?

62
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:26,650
Let's just walk without saying anything.

63
00:03:26,983 --> 00:03:28,083
It feels nice to walk.

64
00:03:29,150 --> 00:03:30,250
Yeah, let's do that.

65
00:03:39,983 --> 00:03:43,083
You thought that, since my grandma
is your maternal grandmother,

66
00:03:43,450 --> 00:03:46,583
we couldn't be together anymore, right?

67
00:03:47,050 --> 00:03:48,050
What?

68
00:03:49,083 --> 00:03:51,983
How could we?

69
00:03:52,683 --> 00:03:56,083
If that were true, we'd be cousins.

70
00:03:57,583 --> 00:03:58,583
Listen carefully.

71
00:03:59,450 --> 00:04:02,183
My grandma remarried my grandpa.

72
00:04:02,583 --> 00:04:03,883
She already had a daughter before that.

73
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:05,750
I'm adopted.

74
00:04:07,050 --> 00:04:10,950
So even though we share the same grandma,

75
00:04:12,050 --> 00:04:15,350
it doesn't create any problem between us.

76
00:04:17,383 --> 00:04:18,650
Should I explain it more simply?

77
00:04:20,383 --> 00:04:23,150
There's absolutely no reason we'd have
to break up because of our grandma...

78
00:04:24,950 --> 00:04:25,983
or anything like that.

79
00:04:28,350 --> 00:04:30,350
I was confused for a while.

80
00:04:32,750 --> 00:04:35,650
A miracle happened
to my mom and grandmother,

81
00:04:38,850 --> 00:04:39,883
and on such a wonderful day,

82
00:04:41,050 --> 00:04:43,083
I suddenly wondered...

83
00:04:44,283 --> 00:04:45,950
what would happen to us.

84
00:04:47,983 --> 00:04:49,950
I hated myself for thinking that.

85
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:53,750
I wondered if we'd have to break up...

86
00:04:55,350 --> 00:04:56,450
after all.

87
00:05:01,550 --> 00:05:02,550
What a crybaby.

88
00:05:09,783 --> 00:05:12,550
Don't let anything shake you.

89
00:05:14,483 --> 00:05:17,850
Believe in me,
and believe in yourself too, Eun Ae.

90
00:05:19,550 --> 00:05:21,650
Okay. I will.

91
00:05:22,983 --> 00:05:24,350
Nothing can shake me anymore.

92
00:05:37,850 --> 00:05:38,850
I love you so much.

93
00:05:39,783 --> 00:05:42,850
My little Cho Eun Ae.

94
00:06:24,783 --> 00:06:25,783
Seung Ri.

95
00:06:26,950 --> 00:06:27,950
What's wrong?

96
00:06:28,950 --> 00:06:31,350
Can you just stay like this
for a little while?

97
00:06:40,050 --> 00:06:41,350
I can't bear to see you fall apart.

98
00:06:42,050 --> 00:06:45,250
No matter what happens,
I'll always be by your side.

99
00:06:46,050 --> 00:06:47,183
So don't ever fall apart.

100
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:49,150
I won't.

101
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:54,250
I'll never fall apart,
so you can let go now.

102
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:59,650
That's right.
That's the Seo Seung Ri I know.

103
00:07:01,250 --> 00:07:02,250
Let's go.

104
00:07:24,350 --> 00:07:25,750
You went to meet that lady?

105
00:07:26,850 --> 00:07:27,850
What did she say?

106
00:07:29,750 --> 00:07:32,650
It seems the Chairman's condition
is much worse than we thought.

107
00:07:34,150 --> 00:07:36,183
She burst into tears
the moment she saw me.

108
00:07:36,850 --> 00:07:38,483
It broke my heart.

109
00:07:41,083 --> 00:07:43,550
But I can't believe myself.

110
00:07:44,950 --> 00:07:47,550
In front of someone who was
already hurting because of the Chairman,

111
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:50,483
all I did was go on and on about myself.

112
00:07:50,983 --> 00:07:53,583
About yourself? What did you say?

113
00:07:56,450 --> 00:07:58,850
I talked about being abandoned.

114
00:08:02,350 --> 00:08:04,483
I even said things
I never managed to tell you.

115
00:08:05,650 --> 00:08:06,950
Things you never told me?

116
00:08:07,683 --> 00:08:09,050
You'd been carrying things like that?

117
00:08:09,783 --> 00:08:10,783
I'm sorry, honey.

118
00:08:13,350 --> 00:08:14,650
There were things that hurt too much...

119
00:08:16,183 --> 00:08:18,850
for me to ever say out loud.

120
00:08:20,850 --> 00:08:22,683
I don't know what came over me today.

121
00:08:23,950 --> 00:08:26,350
For some reason, whenever I'm with her,

122
00:08:27,450 --> 00:08:29,750
I end up telling her everything
in my heart.

123
00:08:31,683 --> 00:08:33,683
Things I couldn't even tell Sun Bun...

124
00:08:34,350 --> 00:08:38,250
after confiding in her for decades
just came pouring out.

125
00:08:41,350 --> 00:08:42,350
She really...

126
00:08:45,350 --> 00:08:47,150
feels like my own mother.

127
00:08:48,983 --> 00:08:50,150
Sounds ridiculous, doesn't it?

128
00:08:51,383 --> 00:08:53,850
Someone like me, who never even had
a mother to go back to.

129
00:08:56,250 --> 00:08:59,350
I guess
it's because she's such a warm person.

130
00:09:02,650 --> 00:09:03,650
Honey.

131
00:09:04,583 --> 00:09:07,650
There's something I need to tell you.

132
00:09:08,150 --> 00:09:09,150
Something you need to tell me?

133
00:09:11,283 --> 00:09:14,183
- Grandma, Grandpa.
- Bit Na.

134
00:09:14,350 --> 00:09:17,583
Bit Na, what's wrong? You can't sleep?

135
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:22,150
No. Grandma, will you sing me a lullaby?

136
00:09:22,550 --> 00:09:23,650
Of course I will.

137
00:09:23,650 --> 00:09:25,750
Let's go. I'll sing you a lullaby.

138
00:09:26,150 --> 00:09:28,083
Right. What was it you wanted to tell me?

139
00:09:28,450 --> 00:09:29,450
What?

140
00:09:30,450 --> 00:09:32,350
It's nothing.

141
00:09:33,050 --> 00:09:34,450
Go put Bit Na to bed.

142
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:36,950
Okay. You should wash up
and get some sleep too.

143
00:09:37,450 --> 00:09:39,183
Bit Na, let's go.

144
00:09:40,683 --> 00:09:41,750
Let's go.

145
00:09:50,983 --> 00:09:52,683
Why are you still awake?

146
00:09:55,050 --> 00:09:56,883
I waited because I have something
to tell you both.

147
00:09:57,683 --> 00:09:59,450
Yes, Father. Please go ahead.

148
00:10:00,150 --> 00:10:01,150
Father?

149
00:10:04,050 --> 00:10:06,650
I was thinking about telling your mom
about Grandma,

150
00:10:07,883 --> 00:10:09,750
but I don't think we need to anymore.

151
00:10:11,150 --> 00:10:14,083
Even after being apart all those years,

152
00:10:14,283 --> 00:10:17,550
they're still deeply connected
in their hearts.

153
00:10:18,083 --> 00:10:19,550
Connected?

154
00:10:21,650 --> 00:10:25,483
For some reason, they feel close,
open up to each other,

155
00:10:25,483 --> 00:10:27,250
and want to lean on each other.

156
00:10:28,983 --> 00:10:31,750
I think your mom
keeps being drawn to Grandma.

157
00:10:32,650 --> 00:10:36,083
It's as if they're bound tightly
by an invisible thread of fate.

158
00:10:37,683 --> 00:10:40,583
I think they'll recognize each other soon.

159
00:10:41,583 --> 00:10:43,350
And I think they'll untangle the knot
between them too.

160
00:10:44,350 --> 00:10:46,150
That would be wonderful.

161
00:10:47,150 --> 00:10:48,883
But do you really think they'll be okay?

162
00:10:49,950 --> 00:10:52,183
I'm worried, but all we can do is wait.

163
00:10:52,850 --> 00:10:55,283
In the end, they're mother and daughter.

164
00:10:56,150 --> 00:10:58,283
Yes, I understand what you mean.

165
00:10:59,650 --> 00:11:00,950
Then the two of you...

166
00:11:03,550 --> 00:11:06,250
Never mind. It's late. Let's go inside.

167
00:11:06,650 --> 00:11:07,650
Yes.

168
00:11:16,550 --> 00:11:17,650
Did you sleep well, Father?

169
00:11:17,983 --> 00:11:20,050
Yes, I slept well.

170
00:11:20,583 --> 00:11:23,783
Father, is Mother still bedridden?

171
00:11:24,283 --> 00:11:25,650
I'll make her rice gruel later.

172
00:11:26,850 --> 00:11:28,450
Did you go for your walk, honey?

173
00:11:29,383 --> 00:11:32,050
Mother, are you okay?

174
00:11:32,350 --> 00:11:33,683
Until yesterday...

175
00:11:33,850 --> 00:11:35,183
I'm almost completely recovered now.

176
00:11:35,883 --> 00:11:38,650
Come on in.
I made your favorite fish stew.

177
00:11:39,450 --> 00:11:42,183
Fish stew? That'll really hit the spot.

178
00:11:42,783 --> 00:11:44,583
Mr. Ju, come join us too.

179
00:11:45,250 --> 00:11:48,450
Thank you for going all the way
to the fish market so early this morning.

180
00:11:50,350 --> 00:11:52,450
Then I'll have a bowl too.

181
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:54,250
Come on in, everyone.

182
00:11:55,083 --> 00:11:56,550
- Yes.
- Yes.

183
00:11:59,383 --> 00:12:01,750
What happened?

184
00:12:02,450 --> 00:12:04,350
How did she recover
so completely overnight?

185
00:12:04,883 --> 00:12:05,950
Seriously.

186
00:12:06,350 --> 00:12:09,650
Did Kang Yeon Ja work
some kind of magic yesterday?

187
00:12:10,550 --> 00:12:12,550
Magic? What kind of magic?

188
00:12:13,550 --> 00:12:15,850
Hey, Ko Min Ho.

189
00:12:16,350 --> 00:12:18,183
It's been hard to see you lately.

190
00:12:18,850 --> 00:12:21,250
How's the competition preparation going?

191
00:12:21,250 --> 00:12:24,983
Yes. As long as the two of you
stay out of it, everything will be fine.

192
00:12:25,150 --> 00:12:27,550
The two of us? Us?

193
00:12:28,950 --> 00:12:31,550
Hey! What are you trying to say?

194
00:12:35,750 --> 00:12:38,450
You should eat breakfast before you leave!

195
00:12:38,950 --> 00:12:40,550
(Kangsu Construction)

196
00:12:40,550 --> 00:12:43,950
Manager Seo found out?
So did you tell her I ordered it?

197
00:12:44,150 --> 00:12:45,950
No, absolutely not.

198
00:12:47,150 --> 00:12:48,350
I didn't say a single word.

199
00:12:51,383 --> 00:12:52,983
But somehow the Chief found out.

200
00:12:54,783 --> 00:12:57,450
He told me to pass this message
to the person who put me up to it.

201
00:12:59,050 --> 00:13:02,350
"If you interfere one more time, Team One
will be automatically disqualified."

202
00:13:02,950 --> 00:13:03,950
What?

203
00:13:05,050 --> 00:13:06,950
That little punk threatened me again?

204
00:13:08,283 --> 00:13:09,550
- What?
- Enough.

205
00:13:10,450 --> 00:13:13,050
Knowing Manager Seo,
she won't let this slide.

206
00:13:13,850 --> 00:13:14,950
Prepare yourself
for a disciplinary hearing.

207
00:13:16,183 --> 00:13:17,183
Sir.

208
00:13:18,483 --> 00:13:21,050
Then I won't have any choice
but to say I was acting under your orders.

209
00:13:21,450 --> 00:13:23,350
You won't have a choice?
Are you saying we'll both go down?

210
00:13:23,983 --> 00:13:26,950
Do you think having you do one tiny thing
is going to hurt me?

211
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:28,883
Let's keep it simple.

212
00:13:29,683 --> 00:13:31,850
You're the only one who needs to go down.

213
00:13:33,583 --> 00:13:34,650
Sir, this is unfair.

214
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:39,283
Please spare me just this once.

215
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:43,850
If it really goes
to the disciplinary committee,

216
00:13:44,550 --> 00:13:46,883
just say you made a mistake
in the heat of the moment...

217
00:13:47,383 --> 00:13:49,850
because you wanted to beat Cho Eun Ae.

218
00:13:52,450 --> 00:13:54,583
You didn't steal
a single piece of information.

219
00:13:55,950 --> 00:13:58,683
I'll make sure this doesn't get
any bigger, so don't worry.

220
00:13:59,850 --> 00:14:01,050
Besides, at worst,

221
00:14:01,750 --> 00:14:04,250
it'll probably end with a pay cut
or a minor disciplinary action.

222
00:14:04,883 --> 00:14:07,050
Do you understand what I'm saying?

223
00:14:07,150 --> 00:14:08,750
Yes, sir.

224
00:14:10,783 --> 00:14:15,550
I expected too much from you. Seriously.

225
00:14:16,150 --> 00:14:18,550
I risked a manager position
on someone who can't even handle...

226
00:14:18,550 --> 00:14:20,183
one simple task properly.

227
00:14:24,050 --> 00:14:25,050
Why are you still here?

228
00:14:25,650 --> 00:14:26,983
- Get out. Now.
- Yes.

229
00:14:29,150 --> 00:14:31,050
I'll make it up to you soon.

230
00:14:32,183 --> 00:14:33,350
Please give me just one more chance.

231
00:14:36,450 --> 00:14:37,450
Another chance?

232
00:14:51,683 --> 00:14:53,683
What are you packing up like that for?

233
00:14:57,183 --> 00:14:58,183
What's that photo?

234
00:14:59,950 --> 00:15:01,283
I heard from the Chairman...

235
00:15:02,950 --> 00:15:05,250
that your wife
is Madam's long-lost daughter.

236
00:15:07,950 --> 00:15:09,483
I still can't believe it myself.

237
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:13,350
They stood face to face
without recognizing each other.

238
00:15:15,183 --> 00:15:16,550
My wife still doesn't know.

239
00:15:17,850 --> 00:15:19,150
That's how frightening time can be.

240
00:15:22,050 --> 00:15:25,083
I used the childhood photo Madam had...

241
00:15:25,850 --> 00:15:27,216
and generated an age-progressed image.

242
00:15:28,583 --> 00:15:32,550
I looked at it countless times myself,
yet I never suspected a thing.

243
00:15:32,950 --> 00:15:35,750
Of course not.
You couldn't have even imagined it.

244
00:15:37,750 --> 00:15:40,583
Give this photo to your wife.

245
00:15:42,683 --> 00:15:43,683
Okay.

246
00:15:46,250 --> 00:15:47,850
You've been through a lot all this time.

247
00:15:48,350 --> 00:15:49,650
I didn't really do anything.

248
00:16:02,683 --> 00:16:03,750
Something's wrong, isn't it?

249
00:16:04,450 --> 00:16:07,650
Is someone threatening you?

250
00:16:10,750 --> 00:16:14,350
Could it possibly be connected...

251
00:16:15,450 --> 00:16:16,550
to what happened 25 years ago?

252
00:16:27,583 --> 00:16:30,450
No. I want to hear more.

253
00:16:31,250 --> 00:16:32,850
I want to hear the rest of the story too.

254
00:16:34,050 --> 00:16:35,050
Sorry?

255
00:16:35,983 --> 00:16:38,150
It's nothing.

256
00:16:39,950 --> 00:16:44,450
Whenever you feel like talking,
tell me everything.

257
00:16:45,050 --> 00:16:46,750
I'll listen to it all.

258
00:16:47,350 --> 00:16:49,650
Your words alone mean a lot to me, ma'am.

259
00:16:50,850 --> 00:16:52,750
Come to think of it,

260
00:16:53,250 --> 00:16:55,450
I heard you're searching
for your long-lost daughter too.

261
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:58,850
Thinking back,

262
00:16:58,850 --> 00:17:00,983
I really said something thoughtless
last time.

263
00:17:02,250 --> 00:17:04,450
When you said your daughter
liked flower pancakes,

264
00:17:05,350 --> 00:17:08,550
I casually said she was lucky.

265
00:17:09,850 --> 00:17:11,150
I'm sorry.

266
00:17:11,850 --> 00:17:12,850
No.

267
00:17:14,250 --> 00:17:17,150
You have nothing to apologize to me for.

268
00:17:18,850 --> 00:17:21,150
May I ask...

269
00:17:23,150 --> 00:17:25,350
Do you remember...

270
00:17:25,950 --> 00:17:28,250
the place where you last parted
with your mom?

271
00:17:29,350 --> 00:17:30,350
Of course.

272
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:33,850
How could I ever forget that place?

273
00:17:34,350 --> 00:17:38,783
Then, why don't you go back there?

274
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:40,483
Why would I go back there?

275
00:17:41,950 --> 00:17:43,850
There's nothing but painful memories.

276
00:17:44,650 --> 00:17:48,383
What if she didn't abandon you?

277
00:17:49,750 --> 00:17:52,483
What if you simply missed each other?

278
00:17:54,150 --> 00:17:55,383
Your mom may have spent...

279
00:17:56,383 --> 00:17:58,983
her whole life searching for her daughter.

280
00:17:59,450 --> 00:18:01,350
She's not that kind of person.

281
00:18:03,250 --> 00:18:04,850
Even if that were true,

282
00:18:05,550 --> 00:18:07,450
it's already been 50 years.

283
00:18:12,350 --> 00:18:14,050
Remember what you told me before?

284
00:18:15,183 --> 00:18:18,183
You said if people are meant to meet,
they'll meet someday.

285
00:18:20,583 --> 00:18:22,050
Please go back there.

286
00:18:23,350 --> 00:18:24,650
Your mom's heart...

287
00:18:25,850 --> 00:18:27,783
must still be tied...

288
00:18:28,850 --> 00:18:33,050
to the place where she lost her daughter.

289
00:18:34,850 --> 00:18:37,450
Thank you for saying that, but I'll pass.

290
00:18:40,450 --> 00:18:42,750
I'm sure you'll find your daughter...

291
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:44,750
because you've never stopped
looking for her.

292
00:18:57,650 --> 00:19:00,383
Why do I keep drifting off
instead of studying?

293
00:19:00,683 --> 00:19:02,350
I just can't concentrate.

294
00:19:10,583 --> 00:19:12,983
What? You want to go line dancing?

295
00:19:13,550 --> 00:19:15,850
Yes. Why? Don't you want to go?

296
00:19:16,483 --> 00:19:19,850
Good grief. When I asked you before,
you kept refusing.

297
00:19:20,650 --> 00:19:23,783
I wasn't planning on going today,
so I didn't even get ready.

298
00:19:23,950 --> 00:19:27,250
What do you mean, get ready?
You look fine as you are.

299
00:19:27,450 --> 00:19:31,383
What are you talking about?
These are my work clothes.

300
00:19:31,950 --> 00:19:34,550
You dress on a whole different level
for dancing.

301
00:19:35,350 --> 00:19:39,050
Just wait. I'll get ready in no time.

302
00:19:39,183 --> 00:19:41,450
I'm here now.
Get changed and come out looking pretty.

303
00:19:42,550 --> 00:19:44,583
Ma'am, I'm going to pick up Bit Na.

304
00:19:45,850 --> 00:19:48,283
You're dressed up just to pick up Bit Na?

305
00:19:49,050 --> 00:19:51,450
Yes. I want her to feel proud
of her pretty aunt.

306
00:19:52,250 --> 00:19:53,383
Thank you, Cho Rong.

307
00:19:54,350 --> 00:19:56,583
I should buy you a nice outfit someday.

308
00:19:56,783 --> 00:19:57,850
You don't have to.

309
00:19:58,050 --> 00:20:00,450
I've been so happy lately
thanks to Bit Na.

310
00:20:05,650 --> 00:20:08,150
Ta-da! How do I look?

311
00:20:08,750 --> 00:20:11,283
My goodness! Is that really you?

312
00:20:11,783 --> 00:20:14,483
Grandma, you look absolutely amazing!

313
00:20:16,250 --> 00:20:19,083
Something definitely happened
between those two yesterday.

314
00:20:19,850 --> 00:20:22,350
Otherwise, there's no way Mother,
who was practically...

315
00:20:22,683 --> 00:20:24,150
on her deathbed, could be this energetic.

316
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:30,550
Don't tell me they recognized each other
and are up to something behind our backs.

317
00:20:33,183 --> 00:20:35,250
Then I can't just sit around like this.

318
00:20:36,150 --> 00:20:39,650
I'll get rid of
that ticking time bomb myself.

319
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:44,450
I'm Silver Crystal.

320
00:20:48,483 --> 00:20:50,083
- To stand out.
- Right, like this.

321
00:20:50,083 --> 00:20:51,350
- Then like this.
- Yes.

322
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:52,550
It'd look cute.

323
00:20:53,283 --> 00:20:54,283
Right?

324
00:20:58,650 --> 00:21:02,050
What were you talking about?
You stopped the moment I came over.

325
00:21:02,050 --> 00:21:04,250
That's none of your business.

326
00:21:04,283 --> 00:21:07,150
How shameless do you have to be
to crawl back here?

327
00:21:07,950 --> 00:21:08,950
What's gotten into you?

328
00:21:09,650 --> 00:21:12,950
If you were coming to class today,
you should've come with me.

329
00:21:13,150 --> 00:21:15,650
Why?
Did you need someone to carry your bag?

330
00:21:17,050 --> 00:21:19,050
When have I ever asked you
to carry my bag?

331
00:21:19,750 --> 00:21:21,283
You always volunteered on your own.

332
00:21:21,450 --> 00:21:22,450
You're unbelievable.

333
00:21:23,050 --> 00:21:26,983
Yeon Ja, I'll keep watch every second.

334
00:21:27,283 --> 00:21:29,383
Don't worry about your hair.

335
00:21:29,583 --> 00:21:30,983
I'm not worried about my hair.

336
00:21:31,850 --> 00:21:33,450
How's your mother-in-law feeling?

337
00:21:33,483 --> 00:21:36,450
Why are you so curious about Mother?

338
00:21:36,850 --> 00:21:38,750
- What?
- What exactly were you plotting...

339
00:21:38,750 --> 00:21:40,183
with Mother yesterday?

340
00:21:41,050 --> 00:21:43,683
You keep coming over
with side dishes and whatever else,

341
00:21:44,150 --> 00:21:45,450
trying to wrap Mother around your finger.

342
00:21:45,750 --> 00:21:47,850
Are you hoping
to get something out of it later?

343
00:21:49,250 --> 00:21:50,683
As if.

344
00:21:51,150 --> 00:21:53,150
Do you think you can just say anything
you want?

345
00:21:53,250 --> 00:21:55,183
Get something out of it? Seriously?

346
00:21:57,283 --> 00:21:59,050
I'm sick of hearing that nonsense.

347
00:21:59,850 --> 00:22:02,550
Accusing me wasn't enough,
now you're accusing Kang Yeon Ja too?

348
00:22:02,650 --> 00:22:04,050
Are you really going to act like this?

349
00:22:04,783 --> 00:22:07,250
How could you suddenly
turn against me too?

350
00:22:08,083 --> 00:22:09,750
You figured it out, didn't you?

351
00:22:10,450 --> 00:22:11,783
My mother and Kang Yeon Ja...

352
00:22:14,150 --> 00:22:16,983
What? Figured what out?

353
00:22:17,350 --> 00:22:18,350
Forget it.

354
00:22:18,850 --> 00:22:22,583
From now on, I'd appreciate it
if you stopped coming to our house.

355
00:22:23,150 --> 00:22:24,783
How can the wife
of an ordinary assistant...

356
00:22:24,783 --> 00:22:26,983
keep coming to the Chairman's house?

357
00:22:28,550 --> 00:22:32,050
I was trying my best to hold back,

358
00:22:32,750 --> 00:22:36,450
but looking at the way you're acting,
I need to settle this before class.

359
00:22:36,450 --> 00:22:37,750
Here we go again.

360
00:22:38,650 --> 00:22:41,950
Why does that old lady roll up
her sleeves every time she sees me?

361
00:22:42,550 --> 00:22:43,950
Hello, ma'am.

362
00:22:44,183 --> 00:22:45,183
Hello.

363
00:22:45,850 --> 00:22:46,850
Hello.

364
00:22:47,050 --> 00:22:50,283
You've all practiced the new choreography
we started this week, right?

365
00:22:50,550 --> 00:22:51,550
- Yes.
- Yes.

366
00:22:51,550 --> 00:22:52,583
My heart goes thump.

367
00:22:52,850 --> 00:22:54,883
- My heart is fluttering.
- Fluttering.

368
00:22:54,883 --> 00:22:56,150
Shall we begin?

369
00:23:14,983 --> 00:23:17,583
Chief, are we doing a rehearsal
before the presentation?

370
00:23:18,450 --> 00:23:21,850
A rehearsal? Of course we are.
Which is why...

371
00:23:22,350 --> 00:23:24,650
How about having Ms. Cho Eun Ae
give the presentation this time?

372
00:23:24,850 --> 00:23:26,483
Me? You want me to present?

373
00:23:27,583 --> 00:23:29,650
No, you should be the one presenting.

374
00:23:29,650 --> 00:23:30,850
How could an intern like me do it?

375
00:23:31,283 --> 00:23:33,850
I'll present the introduction
and the design overview,

376
00:23:34,583 --> 00:23:37,250
but since Joy's integration makes up
a large part of this presentation,

377
00:23:37,383 --> 00:23:39,450
I think you should present that section
as the developer.

378
00:23:39,750 --> 00:23:41,083
What do you think, Assistant Manager Kim?

379
00:23:41,450 --> 00:23:42,850
I agree.

380
00:23:43,450 --> 00:23:45,283
Then, by majority vote,

381
00:23:46,250 --> 00:23:48,650
Ms. Cho Eun Ae
will present the software integration.

382
00:23:48,750 --> 00:23:50,750
Done deal. No objections, right?

383
00:23:51,150 --> 00:23:54,650
You just decide everything on your own.

384
00:23:55,450 --> 00:23:56,783
Then become the team manager
if you've got a problem.

385
00:23:57,283 --> 00:23:58,350
Done deal.

386
00:24:02,950 --> 00:24:04,250
Then that's settled.

387
00:24:04,983 --> 00:24:07,450
Good work, everyone.
That concludes today's meeting.

388
00:24:07,783 --> 00:24:08,883
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

389
00:24:12,783 --> 00:24:14,550
Mr. Han Ji Hun,
could you stay for a moment?

390
00:24:15,050 --> 00:24:16,783
Yes? Sure.

391
00:24:16,883 --> 00:24:19,250
Then I'll head home first.
See you tomorrow.

392
00:24:26,650 --> 00:24:30,183
After discussing it with the Chief,
we've decided to let this matter go.

393
00:24:35,350 --> 00:24:37,650
Thank you, Manager Seo.

394
00:24:38,083 --> 00:24:39,850
We're not letting it go
because you did nothing wrong...

395
00:24:40,150 --> 00:24:42,183
or because it wasn't a serious issue.

396
00:24:43,283 --> 00:24:45,283
It's because we are
in a critical situation right now,

397
00:24:45,850 --> 00:24:48,683
and we have to get through
the second round first.

398
00:24:49,250 --> 00:24:52,050
Yes. I completely understand.

399
00:24:52,883 --> 00:24:54,883
I'll make sure nothing like this
ever happens again.

400
00:24:57,150 --> 00:24:59,250
- You may go now.
- Yes, Manager Seo.

401
00:25:33,750 --> 00:25:35,250
Please go back there.

402
00:25:36,450 --> 00:25:37,750
Your mom's heart...

403
00:25:39,050 --> 00:25:40,950
must still be tied...

404
00:25:42,050 --> 00:25:46,150
to the place where she lost her daughter.

405
00:25:49,383 --> 00:25:50,383
Kang Yeon Ja.

406
00:25:53,750 --> 00:25:55,850
Why did you come back here again?

407
00:25:59,483 --> 00:26:00,550
What were you hoping for?

408
00:26:03,483 --> 00:26:10,383
<i>On the way to Mom's work</i>

409
00:26:13,250 --> 00:26:16,150
<i>White wild rose</i>

410
00:26:30,150 --> 00:26:31,150
Yeon Sun.

411
00:26:42,050 --> 00:26:43,150
Now I'm even...

412
00:26:44,883 --> 00:26:47,350
hearing things.

413
00:27:04,050 --> 00:27:06,783
<i>Calling "Mom"</i>

414
00:27:08,550 --> 00:27:12,150
<i>I quietly picked and ate them</i>

415
00:27:14,350 --> 00:27:15,383
Yeon Sun.

416
00:27:39,083 --> 00:27:40,083
Yeon Sun.

417
00:27:42,183 --> 00:27:43,183
It's me.

418
00:27:45,183 --> 00:27:46,183
Your mom.

419
00:28:11,350 --> 00:28:14,050
(Our Happy Days)

420
00:28:14,483 --> 00:28:17,050
I had my doubts, but you were alive.

421
00:28:17,283 --> 00:28:20,583
Why did you show up now?

422
00:28:20,583 --> 00:28:21,450
Yeon Sun.

423
00:28:21,450 --> 00:28:24,150
There's no Jang Yeon Sun.
My name is Kang Yeon Ja.

424
00:28:24,350 --> 00:28:26,350
I never had a mother to begin with!

425
00:28:26,550 --> 00:28:29,550
Don't ever let me see you again.
Do you understand?

426
00:28:30,050 --> 00:28:31,650
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
